snippet.textDisplay:
TAA, my word. Going through all the major leagues and trying to think of any RB that comes near him, there are some big names who are good right backs but whilst they may be solid defensively or half decent going forward the only one who I think can come close to the overall quality he has is Joshua Kimmich, who has taken the Lahm path of being such a good footballer he is also playing more centre mid now. Something Trent could do.

Also I was surprised about how much better Liverpool were. I mean we all could see this year they are the best side, they are playing well and consistently well. Thought they’d win but this was complete domination. Ominous for the league. It would be a disaster now if they didn’t win it. 18 played, 17 won, 1 drawn, 0 lost.. wow

snippet.textDisplay: Born and bread in Leicester but supported Liverpool since those crown paint days. I'm 41 now and I was at the game in the home supporter crowd last night and cheered everytime Liverpool scored. I'm surprised no camera picked me up. The abuse I got was appalling. But like Henry said in this morning papers. You just have to enjoy the quality of Liverpool. Yes it is going to be our title. Yes we will go unbeaten and yes we will have record points ever. We are Liverpool FC. And to all you Leicester fans leaving early? If you finish in the top 4 this season will go down just aswell as winning the league a few years back. Stop being ungrateful and also enjoy what Leicester are doing. Come on, did you really think you had a chance of winning the league this season? Top 6 is what was aimed for and you are already safe from the drop. Time to stop dreaming of  winning the league and start to dream of CL Football. YNWA
